☁️ What is Cloud Endpoint

Cloud Endpoint usually refers to Google Cloud Endpoints.

Simple Meaning

A Cloud Endpoint is a gateway that manages APIs in the cloud.

Think of it like:
🏢 Receptionist for APIs

It helps:

Control who can access your API
Secure APIs
Monitor API usage
Handle authentication
Example

If you create an API for a Node.js app, Cloud Endpoints can:

Protect the API
Log requests
Limit how many times users call it
Authenticate users
Real-world Analogy

Cloud Endpoint =
📞 Reception desk for your backend services

All requests go through it first.

